 width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sam-fender">Sam Fender</a> has reflected on the death of ex- <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/one-direction">One Direction</a> singer <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/liam-payne">Liam Payne</a> last year – see what he had to say below.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/liam-payne-one-direction-obituary-3803755">Liam Payne 1993-2024: One Direction star who helped spark a pop phenomenon</a></strong></li></ul><p> Speaking to <a href="https://www.thetimes.com/article/2477ea71-a04f-46ee-980e-f2a6dad38df6?shareToken=db88db7b003ab51d0c2f12a93295de6f" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Sunday Times</em></a> about his latest album <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/sam-fender-people-watching-review-3840019">&#39;People Watching&#39;</a> , Sam Fender broke down the themes of several tracks on the record. One of those tracks is &#39;TV Dinner&#39;, which has been lauded since its release as a takedown of the music industry.</p><p> On the track, Fender mentions the late <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/amy-winehouse">Amy Winehouse</a> and the industry&#39;s treatment of her leading up to her <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/amy-winehouse-180-1280292#:~:text=Amy%20Winehouse%20died%20today%20(July,were%20unable%20to%20revive%20her.">untimely death in 2011</a> : “ <em>Like Winehouse, she was just a bairn / They love her now but bled her then</em> “. The same thing tragically happened to Liam Payne, who suffered a <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/one-directions-liam-payne-had-died-aged-31-3803523">fatal fall from a third-floor balcony at the CasaSur Palermo Hotel in Buenos Aires, Argentina</a> last year. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Sam Fender - TV Dinner (Official Lyric Video)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6znfm2sjlmE?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Prior to Payne&#39;s death, the artist was largely criticised by the public just days before the tragic fall as he had <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/niall-horan-recalls-final-goodbye-with-brother-liam-payne-days-before-death-3804102">attended ex-bandmate Niall Horan&#39;s Argentina concert</a> and was mocked for “stealing” the attention of fans who had paid to see Horan. Payne had also had several public battles with addiction, in<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-payne-rehab-stay-viral-one-direction-comments-3467296">July 2023 opening up about a recent stint in rehab</a> .</p><p> Reflecting on Payne&#39;s passing, Sam Fender revealed to <em>The Sunday Times</em> that he had written &#39;TV Dinner&#39; shortly before the tragic incident: “It&#39;s the British culture of building them up to knock &#39;em down.这是狂野的。 I wrote that, then Liam Payne died.” </p><figure id="attachment_3829687" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3829687" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3829687" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images.jpg" alt="利亚姆·佩恩" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3829687" class="wp-caption-text"> Liam Payne – CREDIT: Slaven Vlasic/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> Fender went on to add that he thought Payne was let down by the industry: “You think of the amount of times he was getting dragged through the press and he didn&#39;t help himself, did he?祝福他。我记得看过他在里面的一些视频，就像是“上帝，真是个山雀”。 But the reality was that he was just a young lad, famous far too young, who had addiction trouble — and everyone hit him with the pitchforks.”</p><p> Sam Fender&#39;s comments echo that of <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-darkness">The Darkness</a> &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/justin-hawkins">Justin Hawkins</a> who had previously criticised Payne but <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-darkness-justin-hawkins-defends-criticising-liam-payne-interview-3820812">explained why he isn&#39;t going to remove his posts in light of the singer&#39;s death</a> .</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/sam-fender-people-watching-review-3840019">Sam Fender  - “观看人”评论：反光和敏锐的独立摇滚乐</a></strong></li></ul><p>Back in March 2023, Hawkins shared a video in which he looked at previous interviews that Payne had done, and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4BCj0nTEnE0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">criticised some of his behaviour as coming across as “arrogant”</a> . A large segment of the video centred around the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-payne-tells-logan-paul-one-direction-member-threw-me-up-a-wall-3239096">divisive discussion Payne had with Logan Paul</a> , in which he recalled the formation of One Direction and implied that he was meant to be seen as the main member in the line-up.</p><p> Although Hawkins seemed to defend Payne to an extent – describing him as his “favourite” member and sympathising with him as one whose brand “suffered the most post-One Direction” – the comments made were brought to light once again following the singer&#39;s death.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-darkness-justin-hawkins-defends-criticising-liam-payne-interview-3820812">He said</a> : “It&#39;s really sad what happened to him, but at the end of the day, it&#39;s not going to change my view on those specific behaviours. Everybody&#39;s complex and there are layers to this and laughing at some stuff that&#39;s laughable… that&#39;s what I do. It&#39;s what I&#39;ll always do.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Sam Fender reacts to &#039;Seventeen Going Under&#039; being named NME&#039;s Album Of The Year 2021" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/DOiTh1M6Uhc?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> In a <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/sam-fender-people-watching-review-3840019">four-star review of &#39;People Watching&#39;</a> , Tilly Foulkes wrote for <em>NME</em> : “Reflective, analytical and vulnerable, &#39;People Watching&#39; does exactly what the title may suggest: takes stock of the characters, friends and loved ones who have made Fender the person he is today. He approaches each track with sensitivity as he looks back on his life so far – perhaps even with an inkling of guilt – and contemplates who he may be next.”</p><p>同时，Fender最近<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-planning-next-album-ive-got-a-load-of-new-songs-already-3839928">透露，他已经在进行后续行动</a>，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announces-more-huge-uk-outdoor-shows-for-summer-2025-3837652">宣布了</a>夏季即将在夏季<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announces-huge-summer-2025-uk-stadium-shows-buy-tickets-3814931">即将举行的英国体育场巡回演出</a>的日期，包括8月16日在曼彻斯特的Wythenshawe Park，8月22日，爱丁堡的夏季会议和Boucher Road Players在贝尔法斯特作为8月28日至关重要系列的一部分。 </p><figure id="attachment_3839939" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3839939" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3839939" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing.jpg" alt="Sam Fender performs on Day 2 of Leeds Festival 2023 at Bramham Park on August 26, 2023 in Leeds, England. (Photo by Matthew Baker/Getty Images)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3839939" class